The unit works like a plane’s black box flight recorder - measuring speed, acceleration, smoothness and control, before giving a score for each journey.

Alex found his limited-edition Corsa in nearby Shaw, Oldham, three hours after it was taken - and it later emerged the thief had scored a perfect ten out of ten for safe driving before ditching it.

Alex, from Moorside, Oldham, only managed 7.9 on the way to work. The unit, which allows Alex to monitor his performance via a phone app, means he can earn cashback for good driving.

His insurance firm Carrot said he would be allowed to keep the thief’s score on his record. Alex said: ‘I found it quite funny that he drove better than me.’

