Alex only passed his test in February and it costs him around £2,400 a year for insurance on the Corsa, which is owned by his mother Kimberley, 43, a hairdresser.

They were able to find out from the black box's GPS feature that the car was stolen at 10.55am on May 8 and abandoned around four miles away later that day at 11.12am - 17 minutes later.

