The Corsa, which had its passenger window smashed and ignition tampered with, was left with an estimated repair bill of around £2,000.

His mother said: ‘We were absolutely mortified, it’s our pride and joy. But we laughed when we found it had been driven so carefully. We can only think they’ve driven like that to not arouse suspicion.’

A Greater Manchester Police spokesman said that no arrests had been made over the theft.

